                "name": "USN-4897-2",
                "description": "USN-4897-1 fixed several vulnerabilities in Pygments. This update provides the corresponding update for Ubuntu 14.04 LTS.  Original advisory details:   Ben Caller discovered that Pygments incorrectly handled parsing certain  files. If a user or automated system were tricked into parsing a specially  crafted file, a remote attacker could cause Pygments to hang or consume  resources, resulting in a denial of service. (CVE-2021-27291)   It was discovered that Pygments incorrectly handled parsing certain  files. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of  service. (CVE-2021-20270)",
